The sponges were sampled from very shallow depths between 1 and 2 m in unattached rubble (dead clam shell) and in part of the reef framework (dead massive coral). The specimens were from the reef flat, i.e. from the mixed zone (
Schönberg 2001
), and from the reef crest.
